{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "To reduce delays in the justice system, Mayor de Blasio should consider putting courtrooms on Rikers Island.", "abstract": "Editorial criticizes endemic delays in New York City's criminal justice system, which have resulted in defendants languishing in jails for years without trial; evaluates plan to cut delays by Mayor Bill de Blasio and New York State Chief Judge Jonathan Lippman, saying it can only work if judges, attorneys and correctional officials begin to cooperate on issue; calls for Legislature to adopt bill changing bail system and creating presumption of release for low-level offenders.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "26", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [], "organization": "THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "original": "By THE EDITORIAL BOARD", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/16/opinion/total-failure-on-speedy-trials-in-new-york.html", "lead_paragraph": "To reduce delays in the justice system, Mayor de Blasio should consider putting courtrooms on Rikers Island.", "headline": {"print_headline": "Total Failure on Speedy Trials in New York", "main": " Total Failure on Speedy Trials in New York ", "content_kicker": "Editorial", "kicker": "Editorial"}, "_id": "552ecf2038f0d824112d669b", "word_count": "540", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/04/16/opinion/16thu3web/16thu3web-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/04/16/opinion/16thu3web/16thu3web-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 468, "url": "images/2015/04/16/opinion/16thu3web/16thu3web-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2015/04/16/opinion/16thu3web/16thu3web-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "468"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/04/16/opinion/16thu3web/16thu3web-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2015/0